# 2p_secondary_fire — host. P09 RMB sync test.
#
# Pairs with 2p_secondary_fire.client.shot. Both spawn ~300 px apart on
# the dummy platform and use RMB (BTN_FIRE_SECONDARY) to one-shot the
# inactive slot — host throws a Frag Grenade, client fires the Grappling
# Hook. Each side should see BOTH:
#   - their own RMB-spawned projectile mid-flight (P09 fix #3:
#     non-hitscan visuals weren't shown to the firer)
#   - the remote player's RMB projectile mid-flight (P09 fixes #1+#2:
#     WFIRE_GRAPPLE now broadcasts a FIRE_EVENT, and
#     client_handle_fire_event spawns the visual head)
#
# What the host log should show:
#   - t=120 spawn_proj mech=0 wpn=10 kind=7  (host throws grenade)
#   - t=180 grapple_fire ph=N (RMB)          (would be on the client
#                                              side; host sees rope via
#                                              snapshot's grapple state +
#                                              FIRE_EVENT-spawned head
#                                              since wpn=13 kind=10)
#   - One FIRE_EVENT broadcast per RMB shot.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/2p_secondary_fire_host
network host 24091
name HostA

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Frag Grenades" Light Standard

# Host on the spawn platform; client to the right ~300 px.
spawn_at 2240 984
peer_spawn 1 2540 984

# Aim at the client's chest (slightly above their pelvis).
aim 2540 956

# The networked shot path doesn't tick `world.tick` during LOBBY /
# COUNTDOWN — only inside MATCH. Auto_start is 1.0s + countdown 1.0s
# in shot mode, so MATCH starts roughly at script tick 120. Schedule
# the RMB fire well after that so simulate runs the edge.

at 130 shot t130_pre_match

# T=140-148: host holds RMB → Frag Grenade. Active slot stays primary.
# Holding for 8 ticks gives the network code multiple inputs carrying
# the bit; a single-tick `tap` is brittle because two adjacent input
# packets in the same server poll cycle would have the latest
# (no-button) overwrite the first. The edge still fires only once.
at 140 press fire_secondary
at 148 release fire_secondary
at 155 shot t155_grenade_outgoing

# Client RMB-fires the Grappling Hook at script tick 200 (well into
# MATCH). The grapple head travels 1200 px/s — visible briefly between
# 200 and ~220 on this side as it flies in from the client.
at 215 shot t215_incoming_grapple

# Settle so the grenade explosion / grapple miss fully resolves.
at 260 shot t260_aftermath

at 320 end
